Document: PinJoint2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_pinjoint2d.rst  
Summary: Properties for configuring angular limits, motor behavior, and joint softness in PinJoint2D.  

angular_limit_enabled (bool): Controls whether angular rotation limits are enforced. Default: false. Set via set_angular_limit_enabled(value), queried via is_angular_limit_enabled(). Note: When true, rotation constraints defined by angular_limit_lower and angular_limit_upper are applied.  

angular_limit_lower (float): Minimum allowed rotation angle. Default: 0.0. Set via set_angular_limit_lower(value), queried via get_angular_limit_lower(). Note: Only active if angular_limit_enabled is true.  

angular_limit_upper (float): Maximum allowed rotation angle. Default: 0.0. Set via set_angular_limit_upper(value), queried via get_angular_limit_upper(). Note: Only active if angular_limit_enabled is true.  

motor_enabled (bool): Enables the motor to actively rotate the pin. Default: false. Set via set_motor_enabled(value), queried via is_motor_enabled(). Key Rule: When activated, a motor turns the pin.  

motor_target_velocity (float): Desired rotational speed for the motor. Default: 0.0. Set via set_motor_target_velocity(value), queried via get_motor_target_velocity(). Unit: radians per second.  

softness (float): Determines how much the joint can flex under force. Default: 0.0. Set via set_softness(value), queried via get_softness(). Higher values allow greater flexibility in the bond to the pinned partner.